summary.text: Represents a generic animation.
The function to execute during each animation frame.
Represents an animation that gradually draws an object, typically a line or a shape, over time.
The function to execute during each animation frame.
Represents an animation that gradually erases an object, typically a line or a shape, over time.

Optional configuration settings for the animation.
                           This may include flags like
`remove`

to remove the object from its parent
                           and
`restore`
to reset the drawing range after erasing.
The function to execute during each animation frame.
The object to be animated, typically with a stroke material.
Represents an animation for fading in an object, increasing its opacity from 0 to its initial value over time.
The function to execute during each animation frame.
Represents an animation for fading out an object, decreasing its opacity from its initial value to 0 over time.

Optional configuration settings for the animation, 
                           including flags for post-animation actions like 'remove' or 'restore'.
The function to execute during each animation frame.
A Map to store the initial opacity values of the object's children.
Represents an animation for moving an object to a target position.
The displacement vector from the starting position to the target.
The function to execute during each animation frame.
The object to be animated.
The starting position of the object.
The target position as a THREE.Object3D to move the object towards.
Represents an animation for rotating an object.
The function to execute during each animation frame.
Represents an animation for scaling an object.
The function to execute during each animation frame.
Represents an animation for shifting an object's position.
The function to execute during each animation frame.
Represents a waiting animation, essentially a pause or delay in an animation sequence.
The function to execute during each animation frame.
Represents a group of congruent marks, typically used to indicate congruency in geometric figures.
The number of tick marks to create.
Represents an indicator with a stem and end ticks to mark a specific area or length.
The end position of the indicator.
The start position of the indicator.

Represents an arc shape, extending the basic Shape class.
An arc is a portion of a circle defined by a radius, an angle, and whether it is closed.
The angle of the arc in radians.
Indicates whether the arc is closed.
The radius of the arc.

Represents a circle shape, extending the Arc class.
A circle is a special case of an arc with a 360-degree angle.
The angle of the arc in radians.
Indicates whether the arc is closed.
The radius of the arc.
Represents a line shape extending the basic Shape class.
The end point of the line.
The start point of the line.

Represents a point shape, extending the Circle class.
A point is modeled as a very small circle.
The angle of the arc in radians.
Indicates whether the arc is closed.
The location of the point in 2D or 3D space.
The radius of the arc.

Represents a polygon shape, extending the basic Shape class.
A polygon is defined by a series of points in 2D or 3D space.

Represents a polyline shape, extending the basic Shape class.
A polyline is a series of connected line segments, defined by a series of points.

Represents a rectangle shape, extending the basic Shape class.
A rectangle is defined by its width and height.
The height of the rectangle.
The width of the rectangle.
Represents an abstract shape with fill and stroke properties.

Represents a square shape, extending the Rectangle class.
A square is a special case of a rectangle where the width and height are equal.
The height of the rectangle.
The length of each side of the square.
The width of the rectangle.
Class representing text rendered in a 3D space.
The text to be rendered.
